00:49:05,165 --> 00:49:07,913
Maurice Castillo, Antonio Taylor,

987
00:49:07,914 --> 00:49:10,997
our first-rounder next year
and the year after that.

988
00:49:10,998 --> 00:49:13,454
<i>That's two number ones,
a blue-chip running back...

989
00:49:13,455 --> 00:49:15,080
I know who they are, Max.

990
00:49:15,081 --> 00:49:17,501
Then you know it's a fair offer.

991
00:49:21,123 --> 00:49:22,622
I'm intrigued.

992
00:49:24,081 --> 00:49:26,421
Good. Let's make a deal.

993
00:49:27,165 --> 00:49:29,413
- Well, you gotta give me some time.
- Time?

994
00:49:29,414 --> 00:49:32,122
Sonny, time's one thing
neither one of us have.

995
00:49:32,123 --> 00:49:33,329
Make the deal.

996
00:49:33,330 --> 00:49:34,921
Give me an hour.

997
00:49:35,581 --> 00:49:37,672
We'll give you half that.

998
00:49:44,330 --> 00:49:45,621
What's up?

999
00:49:45,622 --> 00:49:47,830
I just got off the
phone with Max Stone.

1000
00:49:47,831 --> 00:49:50,246
Yeah? How are things in Buffalo?

1001
00:49:50,247 --> 00:49:51,746
Well, I guess you
didn't ask him then,

1002
00:49:51,747 --> 00:49:53,872
when you called him behind my back.

1003
00:49:54,039 --> 00:49:55,496
Max is an old friend of mine.

1004
00:49:55,497 --> 00:49:58,122
He calls me up to congratulate
us on the Callahan thing

1005
00:49:58,123 --> 00:50:00,288
and I express my
opinions on the matter.

1006
00:50:00,289 --> 00:50:02,585
He call you, or you call him?

1007
00:50:02,747 --> 00:50:05,080
It's such a crazy day.
Who remembers?

1008
00:50:05,081 --> 00:50:06,538
Yeah, well, how 'bout
try and remember this,

1009
00:50:06,539 --> 00:50:09,164
I can and I will fire your ass.

1010
00:50:09,165 --> 00:50:10,664
Then do it, Sonny.

1011
00:50:15,414 --> 00:50:16,746
You actually think
I'm gonna give up

1012
00:50:16,747 --> 00:50:18,788
Bo Callahan for
Taylor and Castillo?

1013
00:50:18,789 --> 00:50:20,830
Hmm? Maurice Castillo?

1014
00:50:20,831 --> 00:50:22,329
And draft picks, okay?

1015
00:50:22,330 --> 00:50:23,413
Don't forget the
draft picks, Sonny.

1016
00:50:23,414 --> 00:50:25,710
You do remember what
those are, right?

1017
00:50:27,789 --> 00:50:30,164
All right. Look. It's...

1018
00:50:30,165 --> 00:50:32,246
On the surface, it's not
a terrible trade, but

1019
00:50:32,247 --> 00:50:34,413
why do you think we
need to do this now?

1020
00:50:34,414 --> 00:50:36,746
Because you burned up any currency
this team had this morning.

1021
00:50:36,747 --> 00:50:38,621
Now you have the opportunity
to build it back up.

1022
00:50:38,622 --> 00:50:40,246
And I don't know what your
problem is with Maurice.

1023
00:50:40,247 --> 00:50:41,621
He's a beast.

1024
00:50:41,622 --> 00:50:43,454
Looks like Tarzan, plays like Jane.

1025
00:50:43,455 --> 00:50:45,413
Your opinion. He
plays in my system.

1026
00:50:45,414 --> 00:50:46,454
He doesn't block!

1027
00:50:46,455 --> 00:50:48,413
I don't need him to block.
I need him to run.

1028
00:50:48,414 --> 00:50:50,329
Which he does, like
a bat outta hell.

1029
00:50:50,330 --> 00:50:53,080
Which takes the pressure
off my offense, okay?

1030
00:50:53,081 --> 00:50:57,672
I got 52 Tarzans in that locker
room. I could use a Jane.

1031
00:51:01,497 --> 00:51:04,998
You should at least seriously
consider what I'm saying.

1032
00:51:08,330 --> 00:51:11,621
All right. Get me the
numbers on all their guys.

1033
00:51:11,622 --> 00:51:13,413
We got about 25 minutes
to see what's what.

1034
00:51:13,414 --> 00:51:14,880
Great.

1035
00:51:25,455 --> 00:51:27,538
Mr. Molina. How are you?

1036
00:51:29,497 --> 00:51:31,663
Very good.

1037
00:51:31,664 --> 00:51:34,129
Excellent. That's good.
Good to see you.

1038
00:51:34,455 --> 00:51:36,250
I'll take you inside.

1039
00:51:39,831 --> 00:51:41,455
Right up here.

1040
00:51:42,998 --> 00:51:44,329
Sonny call you yet?

1041
00:51:44,330 --> 00:51:45,746
Oh, not yet.

1042
00:51:45,747 --> 00:51:46,788
What's he doing?

1043
00:51:46,789 --> 00:51:48,496
Well, I'm sure he's
gonna call soon.

1044
00:51:48,497 --> 00:51:51,246
These are our team reps.
This is Wyndham. This is Phil.

1045
00:51:51,247 --> 00:51:53,080
- Mr. Anthony Molina.
- How do you do?

1046
00:51:53,081 --> 00:51:54,913
- Sir.
- How do you do?

1047
00:51:54,914 --> 00:51:56,080
Right up here.

1048
00:51:56,081 --> 00:51:57,163
I'm not sitting here.

1049
00:51:57,164 --> 00:51:58,246
Oh, no, of course you're not.

1050
00:51:58,247 --> 00:52:00,163
You're with the Commissioner,
up in his lounge.

1051
00:52:00,164 --> 00:52:03,255
Here, let me show you the way.
Let's go around here.

1052
00:52:05,539 --> 00:52:07,254
He's even better.

1053
00:52:07,581 --> 00:52:09,752
Mr. Commissioner?

1054
00:52:09,789 --> 00:52:11,288
Hey, Anthony. How are you doing?

1055
00:52:11,289 --> 00:52:13,454
What are you doing in my lounge?

1056
00:52:13,455 --> 00:52:16,163
You guys sure made tonight
a lot more exciting.

1057
00:52:16,164 --> 00:52:17,288
Thanks for inviting me in.

1058
00:52:17,289 --> 00:52:18,496
Enjoy it. Good luck.

1059
00:52:18,497 --> 00:52:20,121
- Will do.
- Okay.

1060
00:52:20,122 --> 00:52:22,413
Can we talk football?

1061
00:52:22,414 --> 00:52:24,246
Just football, for 30 seconds?

1062
00:52:24,247 --> 00:52:25,998
We can always talk football.

1063
00:52:28,497 --> 00:52:30,746
There's a deal on the
table from Buffalo.

1064
00:52:30,747 --> 00:52:32,497
I heard.

1065
00:52:33,581 --> 00:52:35,079
What's the war room think?

1066
00:52:35,080 --> 00:52:36,705
Split.

1067
00:52:36,998 --> 00:52:38,663
Penn wants me to do it.

1068
00:52:38,664 --> 00:52:40,414
But you don't?

1069
00:52:40,497 --> 00:52:41,580
I don't.

1070
00:52:41,581 --> 00:52:42,746
Why?

1071
00:52:42,747 --> 00:52:44,371
Because I know, in
my heart and my gut,

1072
00:52:44,372 --> 00:52:45,913
that if I make this
trade with Buffalo,

1073
00:52:45,914 --> 00:52:49,413
then I don't get to
make a pick this year.

1074
00:52:49,414 --> 00:52:52,079
All I get back are
future draft picks

1075
00:52:52,080 --> 00:52:55,501
for the guy that Molina
brings in to replace me.

1076
00:52:58,330 --> 00:53:00,501
I've been here two years, Ali.

1077
00:53:03,164 --> 00:53:05,084
Two years.

1078
00:53:05,622 --> 00:53:08,288
I've never gotten a chance to

1079
00:53:08,289 --> 00:53:11,414
see what a team I put
together can do out there.

1080
00:53:13,164 --> 00:53:15,630
First year, it's my dad's team.

1081
00:53:15,998 --> 00:53:19,246
Last year, Drew goes down
before I can see what we had.

1082
00:53:19,247 --> 00:53:21,622
Then I get stuck with Penn,

1083
00:53:22,414 --> 00:53:25,915
who I'm still trying to
figure out how to work with.

1084
00:53:26,122 --> 00:53:29,418
This is finally supposed
to be my season.

1085
00:53:30,956 --> 00:53:34,752
I just want the team
that I want. One time.

1086
00:53:34,914 --> 00:53:38,038
So why are you bugging
me if you already know?

1087
00:53:39,998 --> 00:53:41,918
I don't know.

1088
00:53:46,747 --> 00:53:48,838
I'm makin' mistakes.

1089
00:53:53,664 --> 00:53:55,663
Remember the '89 Super Bowl?

1090
00:53:55,664 --> 00:53:57,914
49ers-Bengals.

1091
00:53:58,497 --> 00:54:01,621
Niners down by three,
3:20 left in the game.

1092
00:54:01,622 --> 00:54:05,746
93-yard winning drive, Taylor beats
the weak safety for a 10-yard TD.

1093
00:54:05,747 --> 00:54:08,838
Yeah, but before the drive.

1094
00:54:09,956 --> 00:54:13,246
Joe Montana's in the huddle. Right?

1095
00:54:13,247 --> 00:54:15,204
<i>And unbelievably, somehow spots

1096
00:54:15,205 --> 00:54:17,246
<i>the actor John Candy in the stands.

1097
00:54:17,247 --> 00:54:20,246
He points at him and asks
the guys in the huddle,

1098
00:54:20,247 --> 00:54:23,748
"Hey, isn't that John Candy?"

1099
00:54:25,622 --> 00:54:28,079
They couldn't believe
the balls on him.

1100
00:54:28,080 --> 00:54:31,501
To be that calm, in that
game, at that moment.

1101
00:54:32,247 --> 00:54:36,418
His guys instantly
relax, they march...

1102
00:54:36,581 --> 00:54:38,413
93 yards.

1103
00:54:38,414 --> 00:54:40,830
93 yards.

1104
00:54:40,831 --> 00:54:43,251
<i>Montana throws a little
slant to Taylor.

1105
00:54:44,497 --> 00:54:46,838
<i>49ers win the Super Bowl.

1106
00:54:47,164 --> 00:54:48,580
Great game.

1107
00:54:48,581 --> 00:54:50,797
It was a great game.

1108
00:54:57,497 --> 00:55:00,417
No one can stop a ticking clock.

1109
00:55:00,747 --> 00:55:02,838
But the great ones,

1110
00:55:03,414 --> 00:55:06,585
the great ones always find
a way to slow it down.

1111
00:55:07,664 --> 00:55:10,414
So slow it down, Sonny.

1112
00:55:13,622 --> 00:55:16,588
Okay. I made a decision.

1113
00:55:16,913 --> 00:55:20,830
It's still Callahan. Let's
inform Buffalo that it's a no.

1114
00:55:20,831 --> 00:55:22,581
That is beautiful.

1115
00:55:22,622 --> 00:55:24,246
Okay, Sonny. We're with you.

1116
00:55:24,247 --> 00:55:25,580
Like hell we are.

1117
00:55:25,581 --> 00:55:28,413
All due respect, Sonny,
that is a bonehead move.

1118
00:55:28,414 --> 00:55:30,912
Maybe so, but we're
back on Callahan.

1119
00:55:30,913 --> 00:55:33,912
Do me a favor. Let's put up the
Wisconsin-Ohio State footage.

1120
00:55:33,913 --> 00:55:35,079
Yeah, sure thing, Sonny.

1121
00:55:35,080 --> 00:55:36,954
We've seen that footage,
like, two million times.

1122
00:55:36,955 --> 00:55:39,371
What are you hopin' to find in
it that we haven't seen already?

1123
00:55:39,372 --> 00:55:40,705
I'm just double-checking something.

1124
00:55:40,706 --> 00:55:41,746
All right. Here we go.

1125
00:55:41,747 --> 00:55:45,292
All right, roll it down to the
first time Vontae sacks Bo.

1126
00:55:45,622 --> 00:55:47,463
All right. Here we go.

1127
00:55:49,913 --> 00:55:52,621
Damn. He shook off two blockers
like they were rag dolls.

1128
00:55:52,622 --> 00:55:54,079
And then Bo walks into a bear hug.

1129
00:55:54,080 --> 00:55:55,454
Vontae wrapped him up pretty good.

1130
00:55:55,455 --> 00:55:56,996
Yeah, Bo's hard to sack.

1131
00:55:56,997 --> 00:55:59,793
He was one of the least-sacked
QBs in Division I last year.

1132
00:55:59,913 --> 00:56:01,496
Go to the next play.

1133
00:56:01,497 --> 00:56:02,912
The next sack?

1134
00:56:02,913 --> 00:56:05,664
No. The next play after this one.

1135
00:56:10,747 --> 00:56:12,163
What's he doing?

1136
00:56:12,164 --> 00:56:15,663
He got flustered. Didn't wait
for the play to develop.

1137
00:56:15,664 --> 00:56:17,246
Not Bo's finest moment.

1138
00:56:17,247 --> 00:56:19,996
No. Whatever, it's one play.

1139
00:56:19,997 --> 00:56:22,497
Take us down to Vontae's next sack.

1140
00:56:25,205 --> 00:56:26,955
Ooh!

1141
00:56:27,414 --> 00:56:28,663
Oh, man, that is sick!

1142
00:56:28,664 --> 00:56:32,079
He absolutely bull-rushed that right
tackle. Bo didn't even have a chance.

1143
00:56:32,080 --> 00:56:35,421
Yeah, I gotta give it to the kid.
He's got a wicked first step.

1144
00:56:35,539 --> 00:56:38,004
- See what he does on the next play.
- All right.

1145
00:56:42,205 --> 00:56:44,121
Speed kills. Look at that.

1146
00:56:44,122 --> 00:56:45,912
Yeah, look at that.
He gets frantic.

1147
00:56:45,913 --> 00:56:47,621
My favorite thing about rookie QBs.

1148
00:56:47,622 --> 00:56:50,163
They get frantic when they
think they're gonna get hit.

1149
00:56:50,164 --> 00:56:51,246
Although I gotta give him credit.

1150
00:56:51,247 --> 00:56:52,788
Barrio' those two plays,
he was brilliant.

1151
00:56:52,789 --> 00:56:55,664
He threw four TDs, including
the last one to win it.

1152
00:56:58,080 --> 00:56:59,204
Take us down to that.

1153
00:56:59,205 --> 00:57:00,705
Yeah.

1154
00:57:04,372 --> 00:57:07,997
Looking downfield, staying calm.

1155
00:57:08,414 --> 00:57:10,663
Sonny, this guy's textbook.

1156
00:57:10,664 --> 00:57:14,204
Man, this kid is strong.
That's impressive.

1157
00:57:14,205 --> 00:57:18,547
That's pure Roethlisberger.
He's pro-ready. End of story.

1158
00:57:18,913 --> 00:57:20,413
Take it back.

1159
00:57:20,872 --> 00:57:24,373
Rewind that back to the
start of the play.

1160
00:57:24,706 --> 00:57:26,581
Just stop right here.

1161
00:57:26,747 --> 00:57:27,912
What's missing?

1162
00:57:27,913 --> 00:57:29,037
Fullback.

1163
00:57:29,038 --> 00:57:30,538
But Wisconsin runs most of their

1164
00:57:30,539 --> 00:57:32,246
passing plays out of
an empty backfield.

1165
00:57:32,247 --> 00:57:34,588
No, not what I'm
lookin' at. Try again.

1166
00:57:37,497 --> 00:57:39,372
Where's Vontae?

1167
00:57:42,038 --> 00:57:44,496
You know what, Sonny?
I think he got ejected.

1168
00:57:44,497 --> 00:57:46,413
- He got ejected from the game?
- Yeah.

1169
00:57:46,414 --> 00:57:47,496
For what?

1170
00:57:47,497 --> 00:57:49,329
Yeah, in the third
quarter, after he stripped

1171
00:57:49,330 --> 00:57:51,246
the ball from Callahan
and scored that TD.

1172
00:57:51,247 --> 00:57:52,746
He gave the ball to a fan.

1173
00:57:52,747 --> 00:57:54,580
When he got flagged
for it, he went nuts,

1174
00:57:54,581 --> 00:57:56,371
touched the refs. So
they threw him out.

1175
00:57:56,372 --> 00:57:58,204
Bonehead move.

1176
00:57:58,205 --> 00:57:59,875
Let's see that.

1177
00:58:23,913 --> 00:58:26,663
This is college. What's
he thinkin', you know?

1178
00:58:28,913 --> 00:58:30,913
See? That's it.

1179
00:58:31,080 --> 00:58:32,204
There you go.

1180
00:58:32,205 --> 00:58:34,663
He was showing off. You
can't do that in college.

1181
00:58:34,664 --> 00:58:36,959
You can't hand the
ball to some girl.

1182
00:58:38,706 --> 00:58:41,037
That's not some girl.

1183
00:58:41,038 --> 00:58:43,584
That's not some girl, guys.
That's his sister.

1184
00:58:46,788 --> 00:58:49,414
She died about six months later.

1185
00:58:50,414 --> 00:58:53,414
Boo-friggin'-hoo.

1186
00:58:53,539 --> 00:58:55,704
We ain't runnin' an
after-school special here.

1187
00:58:55,705 --> 00:58:57,454
We're runnin' a football team,

1188
00:58:57,455 --> 00:59:00,871
whose offense was ranked 28th
in the league last year.

1189
00:59:00,872 --> 00:59:03,043
And I still need a runnin' back.

1190
00:59:27,414 --> 00:59:28,580
What can I say, Rich?

1191
00:59:28,581 --> 00:59:31,413
I love being here,
I love feeling the energy,

1192
00:59:31,414 --> 00:59:33,912
and I love having the
number one pick.

1193
00:59:33,913 --> 00:59:35,496
I hope that you would
love having it,

1194
00:59:35,497 --> 00:59:37,580
because you sure gave
up a ton to get it.

1195
00:59:37,581 --> 00:59:39,704
For the record,
I didn't do anything.

1196
00:59:39,705 --> 00:59:41,580
And "ton" is a relative word.

1197
00:59:41,581 --> 00:59:42,662
Playing coy. I like it.

1198
00:59:42,663 --> 00:59:44,912
Come on, just between two
guys, forget the cameras,

1199
00:59:44,913 --> 00:59:46,704
who're you gonna take,
number one overall?

1200
00:59:46,705 --> 00:59:50,704
Well, I think it would be
unsportsmanlike, spoil the surprise.

1201
00:59:50,705 --> 00:59:54,046
Anthony Molina. Not
giving me anything.

1202
00:59:58,164 --> 00:59:59,329
What?

1203
00:59:59,330 --> 01:00:00,413
Just please come with me.

1204
01:00:00,414 --> 01:00:03,005
What? Oh, no, not back in there.

1205
01:00:13,663 --> 01:00:15,209
So?

1206
01:00:16,581 --> 01:00:18,876
So, what do you want?

1207
01:00:21,913 --> 01:00:24,254
Honestly...

1208
01:00:29,705 --> 01:00:32,080
I don't want to be a secret.

1209
01:00:35,164 --> 01:00:36,754
Okay.

1210
01:00:39,872 --> 01:00:41,454
Let's not be a secret.

1211
01:00:45,414 --> 01:00:47,209
Excuse me.

1212
01:00:48,663 --> 01:00:50,496
- Jesus, Rick!
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1213
01:00:50,497 --> 01:00:52,496
The head of security said he
wanted to talk to Mr. Weaver.

1214
01:00:52,497 --> 01:00:54,497
He said it was urgent.

1215
01:00:54,580 --> 01:00:56,745
- Ralph.
- Sonny.

1216
01:00:56,746 --> 01:00:58,204
- Ali.
- Ralph.

1217
01:00:58,205 --> 01:00:59,829
Everybody cozy?

1218
01:01:00,913 --> 01:01:02,413
Good.

1219
01:01:02,414 --> 01:01:06,584
Sonny, if you don't mind, I've got
something for you in my office.

1220
01:01:12,455 --> 01:01:14,413
Got a new Callahan story for you.

1221
01:01:14,414 --> 01:01:16,246
Not sure I want to hear it.

1222
01:01:16,247 --> 01:01:18,912
You know, you hung me out to dry
pretty good with the last one.

1223
01:01:18,913 --> 01:01:20,829
Just talked to Jack
Tate in Washington.

1224
01:01:20,830 --> 01:01:23,246
He said when they found out
they had the number five pick,

1225
01:01:23,247 --> 01:01:25,163
first thing they did was send
a copy of their playbook

1226
01:01:25,164 --> 01:01:26,996
to all the guys they
were interested in.

1227
01:01:26,997 --> 01:01:28,579
Right. We do the same thing.

1228
01:01:28,580 --> 01:01:31,079
No, no, they put a little
special twist on it.

1229
01:01:31,080 --> 01:01:33,579
They tape a $100 bill
to the last page.

1230
01:01:33,580 --> 01:01:34,745
Why?

1231
01:01:34,746 --> 01:01:36,413
So when they're
