that in that time,

1478
01:17:14,620 --> 01:17:17,162
the team picking behind
them can then jump up

1479
01:17:17,163 --> 01:17:20,287
and potentially steal away the
player the Browns wanted.

1480
01:17:20,288 --> 01:17:24,078
It's a situation we saw play out in
2003 with the Minnesota Vikings

1481
01:17:24,079 --> 01:17:28,125
<i>and it happened again in 2011
with the Baltimore Ravens.

1482
01:17:36,662 --> 01:17:38,120
Sonny!

1483
01:17:38,121 --> 01:17:41,871
Yeah, thank God! Yeah, I was
wondering what you were doing.

1484
01:17:42,496 --> 01:17:44,744
Yeah. It's go time, boss.

1485
01:17:44,745 --> 01:17:48,462
Yeah, yeah. What name do you
want the Commissioner to say?

1486
01:17:50,829 --> 01:17:52,329
All right.

1487
01:18:02,996 --> 01:18:04,619
Hey, guys, he's here.

1488
01:18:04,620 --> 01:18:06,911
Sonny, thank God. Where you
been? We're on the clock!

1489
01:18:06,912 --> 01:18:08,744
Sonny, when are we
sendin' in the ticket?

1490
01:18:08,745 --> 01:18:10,245
Yeah.

1491
01:18:10,413 --> 01:18:12,287
I already sent the ticket.

1492
01:18:12,288 --> 01:18:13,744
You did what?

1493
01:18:13,745 --> 01:18:15,578
You sent the ticket?

1494
01:18:15,579 --> 01:18:16,911
It's tradition! We all send it!

1495
01:18:16,912 --> 01:18:18,661
New tradition, guys, all right?

1496
01:18:18,662 --> 01:18:22,753
When this team starts winning,
we'll go back to that.

1497
01:18:30,704 --> 01:18:32,828
And the pick is finally in.

1498
01:18:32,829 --> 01:18:33,995
It's currently being brandished

1499
01:18:33,996 --> 01:18:36,162
by some walkie-talkied individual

1500
01:18:36,163 --> 01:18:38,254
taking it up to the
Commissioner's podium.

1501
01:18:38,496 --> 01:18:42,292
<i>A big, humongous pick for
the Cleveland Browns.

1502
01:18:43,329 --> 01:18:45,828
<i>Now, to find out whose
name is on that card,

1503
01:18:45,912 --> 01:18:49,744
<i>here's the Commissioner ready
to make history in Cleveland.

1504
01:18:58,579 --> 01:19:02,875
With the first pick of
the 2014 NFL Draft,

1505
01:19:04,745 --> 01:19:07,245
the Cleveland Browns select.

1506
01:19:08,662 --> 01:19:12,870
<i>Vontae Mack, linebacker,
Ohio State.

1507
01:19:23,829 --> 01:19:25,412
Yes! Yes!

1508
01:19:31,163 --> 01:19:32,703
These things happen.

1509
01:19:36,912 --> 01:19:39,412
That's what you decided to do?

1510
01:19:45,454 --> 01:19:47,995
An absolute stunner here
at Radio City Music Hall.

1511
01:19:47,996 --> 01:19:50,203
The Cleveland Browns, with
the number one overall pick,

1512
01:19:50,204 --> 01:19:52,494
take Vontae Mack!

1513
01:19:52,495 --> 01:19:54,578
<i>Unbelievable to me
that Sonny Weaver Jr.

1514
01:19:54,579 --> 01:19:56,703
<i>would make a deal of this magnitude

1515
01:19:56,704 --> 01:19:58,245
<i>and come away with this.

1516
01:19:58,246 --> 01:19:59,911
Forget about Vontae
Mack for a second.

1517
01:19:59,912 --> 01:20:01,578
They could have had Bo Callahan.

1518
01:20:01,579 --> 01:20:04,078
He's the surefire slam-dunk
number one pick.

1519
01:20:04,079 --> 01:20:05,661
We all knew it comin' in here.

1520
01:20:05,662 --> 01:20:08,578
If I'm Brian Drew, current
quarterback of the Cleveland Browns,

1521
01:20:08,579 --> 01:20:09,953
I better play good.

1522
01:20:41,371 --> 01:20:43,287
Yeah. No, no. I realize that.

1523
01:20:43,288 --> 01:20:45,162
He wants to talk to him right now.

1524
01:20:45,163 --> 01:20:46,411
Then call me back.

1525
01:20:46,412 --> 01:20:47,452
I'm sorry, sir...

1526
01:20:47,453 --> 01:20:48,870
Just get in the damn car.

1527
01:20:48,871 --> 01:20:50,370
This is Anthony.

1528
01:20:50,371 --> 01:20:52,203
Tell Sonny I'm on
my way to Teterboro

1529
01:20:52,204 --> 01:20:56,795
and I will literally be in his face in
an hour and he will talk to me then.

1530
01:20:56,912 --> 01:20:58,787
I will, sir.

1531
01:20:59,204 --> 01:21:01,578
- Safe trip, sir.
- Thank you, Marvin.

1532
01:21:15,079 --> 01:21:16,624
It's Sonny.

1533
01:21:21,495 --> 01:21:23,578
Sonny Weaver Jr.

1534
01:21:23,579 --> 01:21:26,955
Congratulations, Vontae.
You're a Cleveland Brown.

1535
01:21:27,453 --> 01:21:30,329
I'm a Cleveland Brown!

1536
01:21:30,620 --> 01:21:32,411
Car's gonna be picking
you up in 10 minutes,

1537
01:21:32,412 --> 01:21:34,078
and we're flying you to Cleveland.

1538
01:21:34,079 --> 01:21:35,794
You think you can manage that?

1539
01:21:35,912 --> 01:21:39,253
Oh...

1540
01:21:44,329 --> 01:21:46,874
You need to get back inside.

1541
01:21:47,079 --> 01:21:49,036
What just happened?

1542
01:21:49,037 --> 01:21:51,502
This is the NFL Draft.

1543
01:21:51,537 --> 01:21:54,753
These things happen all the time.

1544
01:21:54,871 --> 01:21:56,870
Now trust me.

1545
01:21:56,871 --> 01:21:59,911
These teams, they don't want
a quarterback that panics.

1546
01:21:59,912 --> 01:22:02,787
I need you to come inside, now.

1547
01:22:08,495 --> 01:22:10,041
Come on.

1548
01:22:20,453 --> 01:22:23,419
You picked Vontae. Wow.

1549
01:22:24,829 --> 01:22:28,704
Three first-round picks to get the
guy I could have gotten all along.

1550
01:22:30,121 --> 01:22:32,703
Jesus, I used to think
I was good at this.

1551
01:22:32,704 --> 01:22:34,452
Well, that remains to be seen.

1552
01:22:35,704 --> 01:22:39,329
Sometimes, the correct
path is the tortured one.

1553
01:22:40,579 --> 01:22:42,661
It's a gift, Sonny.

1554
01:22:42,662 --> 01:22:46,287
You see things other people
don't see. It's one of the things...

1555
01:22:49,121 --> 01:22:52,121
It's one of the things
I love about you.

1556
01:22:57,662 --> 01:22:59,162
Excuse me.

1557
01:22:59,954 --> 01:23:01,619
You're not gonna believe
what's happening.

1558
01:23:01,620 --> 01:23:03,120
<i>You know, I think back, Deion,

1559
01:23:03,121 --> 01:23:07,245
<i>and I go back to 1983 and I start
thinkin' about Dan Marino.

1560
01:23:07,246 --> 01:23:08,911
<i>He was the sixth
quarterback taken...

1561
01:23:08,912 --> 01:23:10,452
Holy shit!

1562
01:23:10,453 --> 01:23:11,536
What's goin' on?

1563
01:23:11,537 --> 01:23:13,457
He's dropping.

1564
01:23:13,579 --> 01:23:14,661
What?

1565
01:23:14,662 --> 01:23:16,870
Picks number two and three
are not Bo Callahan.

1566
01:23:16,871 --> 01:23:18,666
Nobody's pickin' him.

1567
01:23:20,745 --> 01:23:22,536
<i>Just last year.

1568
01:23:22,537 --> 01:23:24,078
<i>Geno Smith drops out
of the first round,

1569
01:23:24,079 --> 01:23:27,162
<i>and there are all kinds of
rumors goin' on right now,

1570
01:23:27,163 --> 01:23:29,833
<i>"Why is this kid dropping and..."

1571
01:23:30,121 --> 01:23:32,411
Everybody's freaking out, Sonny.

1572
01:23:32,412 --> 01:23:35,503
St. Louis went with Anderson.
Miami took Palmer.

1573
01:23:37,370 --> 01:23:38,536
Who's picking fourth?

1574
01:23:38,537 --> 01:23:40,083
Arizona.

1575
01:23:40,579 --> 01:23:42,120
Are they gonna take Callahan?

1576
01:23:42,121 --> 01:23:44,494
They should, but everybody's
off their game.

1577
01:23:44,495 --> 01:23:47,078
Rams and the Dolphins, both
went with their expected picks,

1578
01:23:47,079 --> 01:23:48,828
even though Bo was still available.

1579
01:23:48,829 --> 01:23:51,369
Everybody's panickin' 'cause
Callahan's still there.

1580
01:23:51,370 --> 01:23:55,167
Jesus, what if he drops to seventh?
Seahawks have seventh.

1581
01:23:55,328 --> 01:23:57,203
What if they ended
up with Callahan?

1582
01:23:57,204 --> 01:23:59,870
Well, then Tom Michaels
is the GM of the decade.

1583
01:23:59,871 --> 01:24:03,078
I'm goin' to the can, to throw up.

1584
01:24:03,079 --> 01:24:06,828
Okay. Denver has five.
Jacksonville has six.

1585
01:24:06,829 --> 01:24:08,411
Yeah, but Denver's not
gonna take Callahan.

1586
01:24:08,412 --> 01:24:09,911
They got Herrod, he's an All-Pro.

1587
01:24:09,912 --> 01:24:13,083
So if Arizona balks, then
Jacksonville's all over him.

1588
01:24:13,370 --> 01:24:15,411
Unless they balk, too.

1589
01:24:15,412 --> 01:24:18,870
And our friend Tom Michaels
grabs him at seven. Shit!

1590
01:24:18,871 --> 01:24:21,837
They have that kid GM down in
Jacksonville. What is his name?

1591
01:24:22,079 --> 01:24:23,911
Jeff Carson.

1592
01:24:23,912 --> 01:24:25,078
Rookie.

1593
01:24:25,079 --> 01:24:27,374
Right, Jeff Carson.

1594
01:24:51,954 --> 01:24:53,120
<i>Hey, buddy.

1595
01:24:53,121 --> 01:24:55,536
Holy shit, man. What do you
know? What do you know?

1596
01:24:55,537 --> 01:24:57,128
<i>About what?

1597
01:24:57,328 --> 01:25:00,078
About this! About this thing!
What's wrong with Callahan?

1598
01:25:00,079 --> 01:25:02,244
Nothing. We like Vontae better.

1599
01:25:02,245 --> 01:25:04,744
The Rams took my pick.
Everything's out of whack.

1600
01:25:04,745 --> 01:25:07,290
<i>Well, you still have time.

1601
01:25:08,829 --> 01:25:10,536
Arizona is picking right now.

1602
01:25:10,537 --> 01:25:12,412
You're right. Hold on.

1603
01:25:12,620 --> 01:25:17,536
<i>With the fourth pick
of the 2014 NFL Draft,

1604
01:25:17,537 --> 01:25:19,953
<i>the Arizona Cardinals select

1605
01:25:19,954 --> 01:25:23,911
<i>Robert Starks, cornerback,
Georgia Tech.

1606
01:25:27,579 --> 01:25:30,045
Wow. Arizona went corner.

1607
01:25:30,579 --> 01:25:32,244
Shit. Starks was my backup.

1608
01:25:32,245 --> 01:25:35,119
That's a tough break, but,
hey, Callahan's still in play.

1609
01:25:35,120 --> 01:25:36,786
Who's pickin' fifth?

1610
01:25:36,787 --> 01:25:39,494
The Broncos, and they're
not taking Callahan.

1611
01:25:39,495 --> 01:25:41,786
They got Matt Herrod.
They don't need Callahan.

1612
01:25:41,787 --> 01:25:42,911
Yeah, I think you're right.

1613
01:25:42,912 --> 01:25:44,911
I think they're gonna go with
that big kid outta Oregon.

1614
01:25:44,912 --> 01:25:47,332
Dearborne. Left tackle.

1615
01:25:47,954 --> 01:25:50,870
Well, congratulations, Jeff.

1616
01:25:50,871 --> 01:25:52,911
Looks like you got
yourself Bo Callahan

1617
01:25:52,912 --> 01:25:55,078
to quarterback the
Jacksonville Jaguars.

1618
01:25:55,079 --> 01:25:57,249
You gotta be straight with me.

1619
01:25:57,704 --> 01:25:59,161
About what?

1620
01:25:59,162 --> 01:26:01,995
What's wrong with Callahan?
Why is everyone passin' on him?

1621
01:26:01,996 --> 01:26:03,286
Why did you pass on him?

1622
01:26:03,287 --> 01:26:05,036
I told you. We like Vontae better.

1623
01:26:05,037 --> 01:26:09,286
Damn it, Sonny, I'm about to
be on the clock here. Please.

1624
01:26:09,287 --> 01:26:10,828
What's wrong with Callahan?

1625
01:26:10,829 --> 01:26:12,244
Can I be frank with you?

1626
01:26:12,245 --> 01:26:13,745
Yes.

1627
01:26:15,037 --> 01:26:16,369
I think he's a bust.

1628
01:26:17,537 --> 01:26:18,911
What?

1629
01:26:18,912 --> 01:26:20,202
How? Why?

1630
01:26:20,203 --> 01:26:22,920
I don't know. Gut feeling.

1631
01:26:23,662 --> 01:26:26,536
To be honest, Jeff, it's a
character thing for me.

1632
01:26:26,537 --> 01:26:27,870
But, look, I have other needs.

1633
01:26:27,871 --> 01:26:30,244
So, if you wanna make
a trade for six,

1634
01:26:30,245 --> 01:26:32,411
I can make that happen right now.

1635
01:26:32,412 --> 01:26:34,703
You want six? Who are you takin'?

1636
01:26:36,620 --> 01:26:38,327
<i>I can't tell you that, Jeff.

1637
01:26:38,328 --> 01:26:40,411
The question is, do you
want to make a trade?

1638
01:26:40,412 --> 01:26:43,244
Because if you're not
sold on Callahan,

1639
01:26:43,245 --> 01:26:45,536
you can still come out of here
with a handful of draft picks,

1640
01:26:45,537 --> 01:26:47,578
you look like a seasoned pro,

1641
01:26:47,579 --> 01:26:50,494
<i>and everybody wonders what
you're up to next year.

1642
01:26:50,495 --> 01:26:52,494
I don't know. I don't know, Sonny.

1643
01:26:52,495 --> 01:26:57,541
Look, Jeff, every year someone comes
out of this looking like a donkey.

1644
01:26:57,829 --> 01:26:59,995
<i>- Can you hear me?</i>
- Yeah.

1645
01:26:59,996 --> 01:27:01,578
Good. Because tomorrow
I got a feeling

1646
01:27:01,579 --> 01:27:04,078
it could be you if you
don't make this deal.

1647
01:27:06,996 --> 01:27:09,953
Look, everyone else has a reason

1648
01:27:09,954 --> 01:27:12,795
to pass on Bo Callahan. You don't.

1649
01:27:13,871 --> 01:27:15,586
Give me six.

1650
01:27:17,412 --> 01:27:19,619
Give me six and I'll give you
our second-round pick this year

1651
01:27:19,620 --> 01:27:21,703
and our second-rounder next year.

1652
01:27:21,704 --> 01:27:23,374
Do what?

1653
01:27:23,954 --> 01:27:27,452
Oh! That sounds awesome,
Sonny. What am I, a jerk?

1654
01:27:27,453 --> 01:27:29,828
I'm just spit-balling here, Jeff.

1655
01:27:29,829 --> 01:27:33,411
<i>Two number twos for the
sixth overall? I'm not an idiot.

1656
01:27:33,412 --> 01:27:35,661
I'd give you ones, but
I already dealt 'em.

1657
01:27:35,662 --> 01:27:38,119
Well, you're gonna have
to do better than that.

1658
01:27:38,120 --> 01:27:39,661
Jesus, the clock.

1659
01:27:39,662 --> 01:27:41,161
I know. Denver hasn't picked yet,

1660
01:27:41,162 --> 01:27:43,537
but they will any
second, all right?

1661
01:27:43,579 --> 01:27:46,999
Shit, Sonny, I need more. Tell me.

1662
01:27:47,370 --> 01:27:50,586
What is the very best
that you can do?

1663
01:28:01,787 --> 01:28:03,457
Final offer.

1664
01:28:03,704 --> 01:28:06,327
Take our number two pick this year,

1665
01:28:06,328 --> 01:28:09,119
next year, and the
next year after that.

1666
01:28:09,120 --> 01:28:11,712
That's three years
of number two picks.

1667
01:28:19,245 --> 01:28:23,041
Four. I want your next
four number twos.

1668
01:28:25,287 --> 01:28:27,077
Nah, Jeff, I'm not gonna do that.

1669
01:28:27,078 --> 01:28:29,661
Stay with me on planet
Earth here, all right?

1670
01:28:29,662 --> 01:28:32,378
You know what I just
offered you is fair.

1671
01:28:34,162 --> 01:28:37,629
So, three years of second-rounders?

1672
01:28:37,787 --> 01:28:40,536
That's right. For
your pick right now.

1673
01:28:40,537 --> 01:28:42,202
And you and your guys can regroup,

1674
01:28:42,203 --> 01:28:45,749
figure yourselves out and relax.

1675
01:28:49,787 --> 01:28:52,378
This is a good deal, Jeff.

1676
01:28:54,537 --> 01:28:57,583
This is a good deal for both of us.

1677
01:29:04,453 --> 01:29:05,536
Deal.

1678
01:29:10,078 --> 01:29:12,244
Good, Jeff. You did good.

1679
01:29:12,245 --> 01:29:15,086
Call it in. Call it in.

1680
01:29:16,704 --> 01:29:18,419
Hey, this is Marx.

1681
01:29:21,120 --> 01:29:23,120
We got something, Ken.

1682
01:29:24,036 --> 01:29:26,286
- Cleveland's in this.
- And Jacksonville.

1683
01:29:26,287 --> 01:29:27,787
Okay, give it to me.

1684
01:29:29,203 --> 01:29:31,244
Okay, somebody get me Tom
Michaels on the phone.

1685
01:29:31,245 --> 01:29:33,290
Tell me you didn't
just do that, Sonny.

1686
01:29:35,245 --> 01:29:36,744
Michaels. Tom Michaels.

1687
01:29:36,745 --> 01:29:37,828
Are we on the clock?

1688
01:29:37,829 --> 01:29:39,744
Tell me you didn't just do that.

1689
01:29:39,745 --> 01:29:40,828
We just got the number six pick.

1690
01:29:40,829 --> 01:29:43,452
And, no, we are not on the clock.
Denver's on the clock.

1691
01:29:43,453 --> 01:29:45,744
Okay, so we got six!
Who are we picking at six?

1692
01:29:45,745 --> 01:29:47,411
Rick, can you get Marvin
on the phone now?

1693
01:29:47,412 --> 01:29:48,578
Let me get this straight.

1694
01:29:48,579 --> 01:29:51,578
In the span of one day, you
have managed to burn through

1695
01:29:51,579 --> 01:29:54,786
three years' worth of number one and
number two picks, is that correct?

1696
01:29:54,787 --> 01:29:55,869
Yeah.

1697
01:29:55,870 --> 01:29:57,786
- I quit, Sonny.
- Don't quit.

1698
01:29:57,787 --> 01:29:59,536
I can't coach a team that
doesn't have a future, Sonny.

1699
01:29:59,537 --> 01:30:00,661
That's the way it works.

1700
01:30:00,662 --> 01:30:01,952
I got Tom Michaels on the line!

1701
01:30:01,953 --> 01:30:03,452
Sonny, are we trading six?

1702
01:30:03,453 --> 01:30:05,873
Will everyone please just shut up?

1703
01:30:06,829 --> 01:30:07,910
People, please,

1704
01:30:07,911 --> 01:30:12,162
can I have a moment of goddamn silence
while I do my job here, okay?

1705
01:30:13,911 --> 01:30:16,119
Look. Don't quit, all right?

1706
01:30:16,120 --> 01:30:19,494
Just let me do my job here.
Just let me do this. Don't quit now.

1707
01:30:19,495 --> 01:30:22,995
If, by the end of the night, you
still wanna quit, then quit.

1708
01:30:23,078 --> 01:30:25,286
Just see what I do from here.

1709
01:30:25,287 --> 01:30:27,035
Your show, Sonny.

1710
01:30:27,036 --> 01:30:28,627
Tom Michaels is holding.

1711
01:30:30,328 --> 01:30:32,035
You son of a bitch!

1712
01:30:32,036 --> 01:30:33,786
Anthony, I need five
minutes, all right?

1713
01:30:33,787 --> 01:30:35,703
Five minutes, and
then you can fire me.

1714
01:30:35,704 --> 01:30:37,202
Sonny, you are a dead man.

1715
01:30:37,203 --> 01:30:39,703
Mr. Molina. Mr. Molina.
Look at me. Look at me.

1716
01:30:39,704 --> 01:30:42,161
Just give him a minute.
He knows what he's doing.

1717
01:30:42,162 --> 01:30:43,494
Tom, it's Sonny.

1718
01:30:43,495 --> 01:30:46,578
Jesus, Mary and Whatnot. Do I
owe you a thank you, Weaver?

1719
01:30:46,579 --> 01:30:48,494
Jacksonville's on the clock

